        public abstract Optional<RuntimeException> getError()

      • tryCollect

        public static <V,R,A> Collector<Result<V>,Result.Builder<V,A>,Result<R>> tryCollect(@NotNull
                                                                                    @NotNull Collector<V,A,R> collector)
        Create a collector that accumulates a stream of Results into a single Result containing either: 1. the collected values of the streamed results according using supplied collector 2. the first encountered failure

        This method is indented to invert the relationship between the Result monoid and the Stream/Collector type, such that this transformation becomes easier: List<Result<A>> -> Result<List<A>>

        Type Parameters:
        V - the incremental value
        R - the intended container type
        A - the collector's accumulator type
        Parameters:
        collector - the underlying collector
        Returns:
        if all successful, a Result of a Collection; otherwise, the first encountered failure
